1. Two training modules on RES  for entrepreneurs, local self-government representatives and investors developed (training module on using IPARD support for RE projects and  training module on energy crops);
2.	Two field visits along with practical classes to CHP plants for students from Belgrade and Novi Sad Universities  performed;
3. 29 annual municipal biomass balances and biomass programs and plans developed;
4. 5 trainings in project financing for generation of energy from biomass in farming estates delivered;
5.	5 trainings in energy crops plantations (local potential and specific characteristics for growing such crops, their manner of utilization, incentives, recommendations to producers and local self-government, etc). delivered
6. One cost-benefit analysis for  6 supported CHP facilities completed;
7. One study visit for national partners and relevant stakeholders organzed (Lithuania, Sept. 2018)
8. One biogas CHP facility (totaling 0.2  MW) commissioned (Aleksinac)
9. 3 model projects/initiatives supported
